This is default HTML behaviour. HTML doesn’t consider extra whitespaces when being rendered otherwise the output will get affected by the formatting of the actual code files.This is followed by default unless explicitly setup through CSS. Input fields however will always show the actual value. Below we can see that in edit mode, the input has the exact string with double spaces.This behaviour is consistent throughout the product. We are checking with Product and Design internally to align the expected behaviour and solve this across the products.cc @Dhara Panchal @Mohit Gupta", "mentions": []}, {"author": "Harish Kumar", "timestamp": "2025-04-27T16:03:54.973+0530", "cleaned_body": "{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
